---
By: Ralph W. Emerson
Locus:
  Page: 427
  Verse: 11
Tags:
  - Service
---
7 * Service It is one of the most beautiful compensations of this life that
no man can sincerely try to help another without helping himself. ...Serve
and thou shall be served. If you love and serve men, you cannot, by any
hiding or stratagem, escape the remuneration.
